article.headline: Arizona State 56, California 52
article.story:
BERKELEY, Calif. (AP) -- Jenny Thigpin scored a career-high 12
points and Betsy Boardman added 12 in Arizona State's 56-52 win
over California on Saturday.

Moments after Carrie Buckner hit the go-ahead jumper, Kylan
Loney made a 3-pointer with 1:27 left as the Sun Devils (9-5, 3-2
Pac-10) rallied from behind in the final three minutes despite
shooting 33.9 percent.

Nihan Anaz scored 11 points and put Cal ahead on a layup with
3:01 to play, but Arizona State ended the game on a 7-2 run.
LaTasha O'Keith added 10 points for the Golden Bears (9-6, 2-4),
who lost their third straight home game with their lowest scoring
output of the season.

Loney scored 11 points but also made five turnovers for the Sun
Devils, who outrebounded the Bears 40-30. Cal made 26 turnovers,
including six by Jacqueline Sanchez.
